    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Waist-length army jackets of a particular style and khaki color, resembling jackets worn by U.S. General Dwight D. Eisenhower during World War II. The jacket became standard issue for U.S. troops beginning in November 1944.</Note_Text>
